    {
      "title": "Express (b+c) in terms of b",
      "content": "From $b = 0.82c$, we get $c = b/0.82$. Therefore:<br/>$$b + c = b + \\frac{b}{0.82} = b\\left(1 + \\frac{1}{0.82}\\right) = b\\left(\\frac{1.82}{0.82}\\right)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Calculate the ratio a/b",
      "content": "Using $a = 22.14(b + c)$:<br/>$$\\frac{a}{b} = 22.14 \\cdot \\frac{b + c}{b} = 22.14 \\cdot \\frac{1.82}{0.82}$$<br/>Compute: $22.14 \\times 1.82 = 40.2948$, then $40.2948 \\div 0.82 = 49.14$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Convert to a percentage",
      "content": "$$\\frac{a}{b} \\times 100\\% = 49.14 \\times 100\\% = 4914\\%$$<br/><strong>D</strong> is correct."
